lib/Algebra/Divisibility/Basic.html#DecompositionMonoid.primal\"><span class=\"name\">DecompositionMonoid</span>.<span class=\"name\">primal</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#Semigroup\">Semigroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[self : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Divisibility/Basic.html#DecompositionMonoid\">DecompositionMonoid</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(a : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Divisibility/Basic.html#IsPrimal\">IsPrimal</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/b5eba595428809e96f3ed113bc7ba776c5f801ac/Mathlib/Algebra/Divisibility/Basic.lean#L124-L124","name":"DecompositionMonoid.mk","line":124,"kind":"ctor","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/Divisibility/Basic.html#DecompositionMonoid.mk","doc":""},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Divisibility/Basic.html#DecompositionMonoid.mk\"><span class=\"name\">DecompositionMonoid</span>.<span class=\"name\">mk</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#Semigroup\">Semigroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(primal : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">a</span> : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Divisibility/Basic.html#IsPrimal\">IsPrimal</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Divisibility/Basic.html#DecompositionMonoid\">DecompositionMonoid</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/b5eba595428809e96f3ed113bc7ba776c5f801ac/Mathlib/Algebra/Divisibility/Basic.lean#L124-L125","name":"DecompositionMonoid","line":124,"kind":"class","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/Divisibility/Basic.html#DecompositionMonoid","doc":"A monoid is a decomposition monoid if every element is primal. An integral domain whose\nmultiplicative monoid is a decomposition monoid, is called a pre-Schreier domain; it is a\nSchreier domain if it is moreover integrally closed. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">class</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Divisibility/Basic.html#DecompositionMonoid\"><span class=\"name\">DecompositionMonoid</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#Semigroup\">Semigroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/b5eba595428809e96f3ed113bc7ba776c5f801ac/Mathlib/Algebra/Divisibility/Basic.lean